{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17527307","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17527307"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T15:30:30+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T15:30:30+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14201"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"14201","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/14201"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.02,0.01,0.82,0.14,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"6887"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"102776"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"6887","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6887"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14201"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"85259"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"12"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"98"},{"type":"tags","id":"928"},{"type":"tags","id":"1804"},{"type":"tags","id":"4986"},{"type":"tags","id":"4991"},{"type":"tags","id":"5351"},{"type":"tags","id":"5810"},{"type":"tags","id":"5981"},{"type":"tags","id":"11622"},{"type":"tags","id":"11645"},{"type":"tags","id":"11648"},{"type":"tags","id":"12729"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"15743"},{"type":"contributions","id":"29688"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43503"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"102776","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/102776"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 62-year-old Aboriginal woman presents to the General Practice clinic with a three-week history of worsening joint pain in her hands and knees. She has a medical history of type 2 diabetes and hypertension. Her regular medications include metformin and perindopril. She mentions that she has been using a traditional bush medicine remedy made from eucalyptus leaves to manage her pain.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, she appears well. Her pulse rate is 72/min, blood pressure 138/85 mmHg, respiratory rate 16/min, SpO2 98% on room air, and temperature 36.7\u00b0C. There is mild swelling and tenderness in the small joints of her hands and both knees.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate approach to discussing her use of bush medicine?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Advise her to stop using bush medicine immediately","Ignore the mention of bush medicine and focus solely on Western treatments","Ask her to explain more about the bush medicine and how it helps her","Tell her that bush medicine is not scientifically proven and should be avoided","Suggest she use bush medicine instead of prescribed medications"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe most appropriate approach in this scenario is to \u003Cstrong\u003Eask her to explain more about the bush medicine and how it helps her\u003C/strong\u003E. This response demonstrates respect for the patient\u0027s cultural practices and traditional knowledge while opening a dialogue about her health management. It allows the healthcare provider to gather more information about the specific remedy being used and its perceived effects, which can inform a more holistic approach to care.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAdvising her to stop using bush medicine immediately\u003C/strong\u003E would be culturally insensitive and could damage the therapeutic relationship. It fails to acknowledge the importance of traditional healing practices in Aboriginal culture and may lead to the patient feeling dismissed or misunderstood.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIgnoring the mention of bush medicine and focusing solely on Western treatments\u003C/strong\u003E misses an opportunity to engage with the patient\u0027s cultural practices and may lead to incomplete or ineffective care. It\u0027s important to consider all aspects of a patient\u0027s health management, including traditional remedies.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESuggesting she use bush medicine instead of prescribed medications\u003C/strong\u003E would be inappropriate and potentially dangerous. The goal should be to find a balance between traditional and Western medicine, not to replace one with the other entirely.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETelling her that bush medicine is not scientifically proven and should be avoided\u003C/strong\u003E is dismissive of traditional knowledge and cultural practices. It could alienate the patient and discourage her from sharing important information about her health practices in the future.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBy asking about her use of bush medicine, the healthcare provider can gain insight into the patient\u0027s beliefs and practices, assess for any potential interactions with her prescribed medications, and work collaboratively with the patient to develop a treatment plan that respects her cultural practices while ensuring safe and effective management of her health conditions. This approach aligns with principles of cultural safety and patient-centered care, which are particularly important when working with Indigenous patients.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Bush medicine is an important aspect of traditional Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander healing practices and should be respected by healthcare providers.","Effective communication and cultural safety are crucial when discussing traditional healing practices with Indigenous patients.","Integration of traditional and Western medicine can improve health outcomes for Indigenous patients when approached collaboratively."],"references":["Aboriginal Traditional Medicine: A Holistic Approach to Healing. Muru Mittigar. 2025. [webpage] \u003Chttps://www.murumittigar.com.au/aboriginal-traditional-medicine-a-holistic-approach-to-healing/\u003E"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"85259"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14201"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"85259","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/85259"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-05-15T14:43:58+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-05-15T14:45:03+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"6887"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"102776"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"12","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/12"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc4b","name":"Rheumatology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:47+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"66","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/66"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Management","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"72",